<br>
-there are players, that want to keep more time reserved for RL. So they never play long sessions.<br>
-there are players who got sick and tired of LFG or starting to make their own group. Despite what some people say, some servers really got a problem.<br>
-there are players, that for some reason have to go often afk during playing, which means, a group really don't like to have them.<br>
<br>
Only things this change will do:<br>
- force that 1 percent of the die-hard solo-ers to find another way of earning the same xp, they got now.<br>
- Make the gap between the classes(or players) that have trouble to find groups and ones that don't have that problem like 3 times as big.<br>
- Make the gap between casual players and others bigger, means casual players will get it slowly a bit more difficult to group, unless with other casuals, because real fanatics rather have people in their group with loads of aa.<br>
-Make the gap between &quot;uber&quot; players and normal players bigger, which will undoubtly lead to other nerves in the future.(since soe will realize some things are too easy with loads of aa)<br>
<br>
But will this change stimulate grouping? Nah, not that much, maybe on lower lvl it will, since the people solo-ing on low level are mostly twinks, who just want a new char high lvl as fast as possible. (guess they will now plevel a group of lowbie's together instead of solo)<br>
<br>
People that already group, will keep grouping. People that can't group that much, will still see the same problems. Only a very minor part of the eq population will change their attitude from solo to groups.<br>
<br>
IF soe really wants to improve grouping, i suggest they increase the groupsize without penalty, like raid system does. So more people will get a chance to form a group.<br>
Or adapt a lot of zones, so there are more group kiting spots around...<br>
