 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaelonxerxentis>Kaelon Xerxentis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/3/03 10:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Understanding Casual and Hardcore Gamers</span><hr size=1> As it stands right now, the only gap between hardcore players and casual gamers is expressed as a function of equipment and ability, which in turn, are largely a consequence of the amount of experience you get. Higher level characters, with more AAs, have an easier time getting into sub-uber or uber-crossing guilds that can equip them with what uber-guilds seek (keys, prereq. flags, etc.). With a greater experience pool being fed to all players, in all locations, simply on the basis of grouping, you have a very real, concrete hope of seeing a lot of casual gamers and role players hit their 60s faster and with greater enthusiasm. <br>
<br>
There's nothing more discouraging than to talk to sarcastic and negative Level 65 players -- and I've seen more and more of them these days. I have to think that the leveling grudge combined with prerequisite hard raiding schedules must have contributed at least partly to this mentality. <br>
<br>
You make leveling easier, you bring more fun to more people without removing end-game challenges and competitive encounters. And for EverQuest to survive against its future competition, it needs to appeal to people who aren't willing to put 8+ hours a day into the game. And this crowd is constituting an ever larger majority as the population continues to shift towards player base retention as opposed to fast-paced growth. It's a simple matter of economics and good business planning.<br>
<br>
The game will get easier. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tigertailz>tigertailz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 530<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/3/03 11:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> trust me the last thing you want is to get to the 'end game'.....the elementals are the biggest abortion ever....so many people quit when they get there it isn't even funny anymore.........<br>
