<br>
However, given the large disparity between full group xp and solo xp, SoE must address the groupability of classes quickly.  Unless they do, in 6 months here is what I predict:<br>
-- more lvl 65 holy trinity classes<br>
-- less lvl 65 traditional solo classes<br>
-- less short durtation casual players<br>
<br>
Here is why:<br>
-- On many servers, the lower level players are alternates for higher level characters.    For many of them, the objective is to level up quickly.  Since the full group bonus will allow you to level at least 80 percent faster than solo, efforts to make them will be higher.  Right now it is a 20 percent bonus over solo for a full group.  Now it is 80 percent.   This is 50 percent more xp per hour than before for the group of 6.<br>
-- Casual style players who are good in groups will quickly be out of level range of the other chars in their normal group.  A casual player may only spend one hour online -- 30 minutes of which will be lfg and getting in group.   But their group mates from the previous session might have been online for 2, 3 and 4 hours respectively.   Given that, in only a few hours, they might be a few levels beyond them.  While this could happen currently, it takes much longer for a player to advance out of your level range for groupablility than it will after this change.  This will further add to the time it takes for a casual player to get a group.<br>
-- This will further re-enforce the holy trinity groups.    From a grouping perspective (and yes I have most of my xp from friends groups) -- tank/cleric/chanter-slower/3xdmg chain pulling groups have been the best xp.   The only exception was aoe centric groups.  When KEI level range gets implmented, the wizard will spend significant time nearly oom.  While the twinked melee will still be doing major dmg.<br>
<br>
To prove the first 2 points on the list -- 6 months from now I will do the following test:<br>
-- Get a list of how many lvl 65 holy trinity classes there are today.  These will be cleric, enchanter/shaman, plate tank (war/sk/pal).   Get a similar list for the less group friendly classes:  necro, wiz, druid (druids have problems post 50), etc.<br>
<br>
-- Repeat this same list after 6 months.  <br>
<br>
If the number of new lvl 65 of the group desirable/necessary classes is far higher than the more solo dependant ones, 2 or the 3 points will be proven.   The last prediction of casual players becoming discouraged will be harder to prove.<br>
<br>
<br>
lvl 65 arcanist<br>
